---
alwaysApply: true
---
- Ensure a README.md file exists at the root of the project. 
- The README.md must always include:
    - Project overview and purpose
    - Technology stack used
    - Project folder structure
    - List of all API endpoints
    - Local development setup instructions
    - Instructions on how to run tests (pytest + coverage)
    - Deployment information (Cloud Run URL placeholder or actual link)
    - Current implementation status (completed vs pending endpoints)
    - Team member roles
- Update the README.md whenever:
    - An API endpoint is added, modified, or removed
    - The project structure changes
    - Dependencies or environment setup change
    - Deployment configuration changes
- Do not generate or modify application code that affects any of these areas without also updating the README.md.
